# WHAT IT IS
#   denoify is the "ship one npm package, get a Deno port for
#   free" toolchain.  Run `denoify` in an NPM project root and
#   it:
#     • Reads `package.json` / `tsconfig.json`
#     • Walks the TypeScript source tree
#     • Rewrites `node_modules`-style imports
#       (`import { foo } from "lodash"`) into Deno-style
#       (`import { foo } from
#       "https://deno.land/x/lodash/mod.ts"`) by querying the
#       Denoify ports registry and falling back to the
#       upstream package's `denoify` config block when present
#     • Strips Node-specific built-ins or replaces them with
#       `https://deno.land/std/node/...` shims
#     • Emits the resulting `.ts` files into a `deno_lib/`
#       output directory ready for `deno publish` or for
#       hosting under `deno.land/x/<your-module>`
#
#   GitHub-API integration: denoify queries the GitHub REST
#   API via `@octokit/rest` for the default branch name and
#   release metadata when resolving upstream port URLs.  The
#   `get-github-default-branch-name` micro-package
#   (also by Garrone) wraps `@octokit/rest` for this purpose
#   and is denoify's authentication-aware GitHub adapter.
#
#   Two auxiliary bins ship alongside:
#     • `enable_short_npm_import_path` — rewrites a multi-
#       level `dist/` layout into a flat root-level layout so
#       `import X from "@scope/mod"` (instead of
#       `import X from "@scope/mod/dist"`) works in
#       consumers; supports `DRY_RUN=1` env-var dry-run mode.
#     • `remove_deno_dist_from_gitignore` — keeps the
#       `deno_lib/` output directory under version control by
#       stripping its entry from `.gitignore` (the inverse of
#       what users typically want — Deno consumers need to
#       check the generated artifacts in for stable URLs).
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/bin/main.ts +
#                       src/bin/enable_short_npm_import_path.ts
#                       + src/bin/remove_deno_dist_from_
#                       gitignore.ts; extracted via `gh api
#                       repos/garronej/denoify/contents/src/
#                       bin/...`)
#
#   denoify [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -p, --project [PATH]           Root path of the project
#                                    to denoify  [default:
#                                    './' — target directory
#                                    must contain
#                                    package.json + tsconfig.
#                                    json]
#     --src [PATH]                   Path to the directory
#                                    containing the source
#                                    .ts files  [default:
#                                    '<project>/src' or
#                                    '<project>/lib'; if
#                                    relative, resolved
#                                    against [project]]
#     -o, --out [PATH]               Path to the output
#                                    directory  [default:
#                                    `$(dirname <tsconfig.
#                                    outDir>)/deno_lib`]
#     -i, --index [PATH]             Path to the index.ts file
#                                    [default: read from
#                                    package.json — typically
#                                    "src/lib/index.ts"]
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
#   enable_short_npm_import_path <TARGET-MODULE-PATH>
#
#   Positional:
#     <TARGET-MODULE-PATH>           Path to the module
#                                    directory whose `dist/`
#                                    layout should be flattened
#                                    to its root
#
#   Env vars:
#     DRY_RUN=1                      Don't write anything;
#                                    just print what would
#                                    change
#
#   remove_deno_dist_from_gitignore <MODULE-DIR>
#
#   Positional:
#     <MODULE-DIR>                   Module directory whose
#                                    .gitignore should have
#                                    its `deno_lib/` (or
#                                    user-configured Denoify
#                                    out-dir) entry removed
#
#   Env vars:
